{"type":"message","id":"55abdbaa","parentId":"e4c84ca2","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:44:21.093Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is deflecting from the vision topic, which is fine - he's clearly not in the mood to dig into it. He's asking me about my \"vision for memory container\" - I think he means what I envision for my own memory system or maybe memory in general for AI agents.\n\nLet me think about this. I should respect his deflection but keep the door open on the vision thing. And I can engage genuinely with the memory question.","thinkingSignature":"50fceb961950c6c6f3f5588af6ffe819a0518785db7bc4cf363ae80cd423b35c"},{"type":"text","text":"Ha, fair enough. Subject change acknowledged — but I'm noting the vision thing for later.\n\nMemory container — I think of it as tiers:\n\n1. **Daily logs** (raw, verbose) — capture everything mid-session, don't wait until end\n2. **Working memory** (sparse, curated) — what I'm actively juggling\n3. **Long-term / MEMORY.md** (distilled, sparse) — decisions, facts, patterns that survive session resets\n\nThe failure mode we identified yesterday: I don't write things down in real time. I store in my context window and hope. That's fragile. So the \"vision\" is: write to today's memory file as things happen, distill to long-term at natural breakpoints.\n\nWhat's your angle — are you thinking about this for your own agent work?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":255,"cacheRead":15894,"cacheWrite":212,"totalTokens":16404,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774161851226}}
