{"type":"message","id":"b6158b78","parentId":"62d5afde","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:56:27.424Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to apply my suggestions to schemocker. Let me think about what I can actually do:\n\n1. Landing page - I can create an HTML file\n2. Sharpen the README positioning - I can edit it\n3. Mac/Linux binaries - I can't build those\n4. Fake testimonials - I shouldn't create fake testimonials, that's dishonest\n5. MCP angle - I can emphasize this in the README\n\nLet me think about what's actually useful:\n- Create a landing page (index.html) that shows the product well with a demo\n- Rewrite the README to be punchier\n- Remove the fake testimonials\n\nBut wait - the repo is `schemocker` but the README talks about `schemock-app`. The clone went to schemocker but the project seems to be `schemock-app`. Let me check the actual repo structure.\n\nActually the README was fetched from the repo and it mentions `schemock-app` throughout. So it seems like the project might be in a different repo or the structure is off. \n\nI should focus on what I can actually deliver: a landing page as an HTML file, a tightened README, removing the fake testimonials, and highlighting the MCP angle. Let me check the directory structure first to understand what I'm working with.","thinkingSignature":"87e6775e50b839dece3ed98ebbd67bbfa51e402f60fc1434b11ae2b273cfe53f"},{"type":"text","text":"Yeah, let me get in there and work. First let me check the actual repo structure:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z5plwsruqjee_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"dir schemocker /b"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":311,"cacheRead":12454,"cacheWrite":19755,"totalTokens":32563,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774162573670}}
