{"type":"message","id":"96e188e5","parentId":"1fbbc648","timestamp":"2026-03-22T07:00:44.680Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. README went from wall-of-text (1350+ lines) to 9KB tight doc. index.html is a solid 24KB landing page.\n\nLet me now summarize what I did for Zach.","thinkingSignature":"5d64a2f60fdd7f6b13868b91e6142010b67c338ed5a710278d8c6c2faaa254f2"},{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what I changed:\n\n**Landing page (`index.html`)** — new file, 24KB:\n- Clean dark theme with the pitch front and center\n- Animated terminal demo showing the exact flow\n- Stats bar (60s, 0 deps, 176 tests)\n- Feature cards (schema-as-truth, hot reload, realistic data, MCP, scenarios)\n- MCP section highlighted as the wedge\n- Scenario preview cards\n- Tight comparison table (3 competitors, 5 rows)\n- Real install commands, real download links\n\n**README (`README.md`)** — rebuilt, went from ~1350 lines to ~9KB:\n- Removed the fake testimonial section entirely\n- Removed the defensive \"why not hardcode\" walls of text\n- Cut the comparison table from 10-row monster to 5-row truth table\n- Moved MCP to the top half as a headline feature\n- Lead with 3-command quick start, not feature walls\n- Scenarios get their own clean section\n- Docs organized by what you actually need\n\n**What I didn't touch:**\n- Code or tests (didn't want to break anything)\n- The MCP server itself (it's already there)\n- Commercial/license docs (those are fine)\n\nWant me to commit and push these changes, or do you want to review first?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34504,"output":315,"cacheRead":12454,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47273,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774162833475}}
