{"type":"message","id":"326dc77d","parentId":"f302c9d2","timestamp":"2026-03-22T07:55:55.980Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to integrate this into the schema routes. Let me look at the server.ts to understand how the server is initialized and how state is managed.","thinkingSignature":"b8a96de928d024a01eb1ad4e061c3b6793c5346890b27e7f7395b37374d86d61"},{"type":"text","text":"\nNow let me look at how the server initializes to find the right integration point:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_25o4rlxu9gqo_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\dev\\schemock-app\\src\\generators\\server.ts","limit":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49952,"output":102,"cacheRead":12454,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62508,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774166152447}}
{"type":"message","id":"7046cd93","parentId":"326dc77d","timestamp":"2026-03-22T07:55:55.987Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_25o4rlxu9gqo_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import express, { Application, Request, Response, NextFunction } from 'express';\nimport { Server } from 'http';\nimport {\n  ServerOptions,\n  RouteConfig,\n  MockServerConfig,\n  RouteRequest,\n  ServerState,\n  JSONValue,\n  Schema\n} from '../types';\nimport { PortError, ServerError, ValidationError } from '../errors';\nimport { log, setLogLevel } from '../utils/logger';\nimport { validateData } from '../utils/validation';\nimport { validateMockServerConfig, createConfig } from '../utils/config';\nimport { setupAllMiddleware } from './middleware';\nimport { setupSystemRoutes } from './route-setup';\nimport { addBranding } from './response-utils';\nimport {\n  determineResourceName,\n  determineBasePath,\n  createRouteHandler,\n  generateCustomRoutes,\n  generateCrudRoutes\n} from './schema-routes';\n\n/**\n * A mock server generator that creates and manages an Express server with configurable routes.\n *\n * This class provides functionality to start, stop, restart, and manage a mock API server\n * based on JSON Schema configurations. It supports custom routes, CRUD operations, response\n * delays, error scenarios, and request validation.\n */\nexport class ServerGenerator {\n  private app: Application;\n  private config: MockServerConfig;\n  private server: Server | null = null;\n  private state: ServerState = {};\n  private version = require('../../package.json').version;\n  private connections: Set<unknown> = new Set();\n  private isStopping = false;\n  private skipValidation: boolean;\n\n  /**\n   * Creates a new ServerGenerator instance.\n   *\n   * @param config - The mock server configuration containing server settings and route definitions\n   * @param skipValidation - If true, skips configuration validation (for internal use only)\n   * @throws {ValidationError} When configuration validation fails and skipValidation is false\n   */\n  constructor(config: MockServerConfig, skipValidation: boolean = false) {\n    // Validate configuration at startup (addresses issue 8.2)\n    // Skip validation for internally-generated configs to maintain backward compatibility\n    this.skipValidation = skipValidation;\n    this.config = skipValidation ? config : validateMockServerConfig(config);\n    this.app = express();\n\n    // Set log level from config\n    if (this.config.server.logLevel) {\n      setLogLevel(this.config.server.logLevel);\n    }\n\n    this.setupMiddleware();\n    this.setupRoutes();\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Configures and applies all middleware to the Express application.\n   *\n   * Sets up CORS, request parsing, logging, and other middleware based on configuration.\n   */\n  private setupMiddleware(): void {\n    setupAllMiddleware(this.app, {\n      cors: this.config.server.cors,\n      hideBranding: this.config.server.hideBranding,\n      logLevel: this.config.server.logLevel,\n      version: this.version\n    });\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Configures all routes on the Express application.\n   *\n   * Iterates through route configurations and sets up system routes like\n   * playground, health check, and gallery.\n   */\n  private setupRoutes(): void {\n    // Setup each route from the config\n    Object.entries(this.config.routes).forEach(([_, routeConfig]) => {\n      this.setupRoute(routeConfig);\n    });\n\n    // Setup system routes (playground, health, share, gallery, etc.)\n    setupSystemRoutes(this.app, this.config, this.version);\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Configures a single route on the Express application.\n   *\n   * @param routeConfig - The route configuration including path, method, response, and options\n   * @throws {ServerError} When an unsupported HTTP method is specified\n   */\n  private setupRoute(routeConfig: RouteConfig): void {\n    const { path, method, response, statusCode = 200, delay = 0, headers = {}, schema } = routeConfig;\n\n    const routeHandler = async (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n      const startTime = Date.now();\n      const scenario = this.config.server.scenario;\n\n      try {\n        // Apply delay if specified or if scenario is slow\n        let effectiveDelay = delay;\n        if (scenario === 'slow' || scenario === 'sad-path') {\n          // Add extra delay for slow scenarios (1000ms to 3000ms)\n          effectiveDelay += 1000 + Math.random() * 2000;\n        }\n\n        if (effectiveDelay > 0) {\n          await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, effectiveDelay));\n        }\n\n[419 more lines in file. Use offset=121 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774166155985}}
{"type":"message","id":"8ec37082","parentId":"7046cd93","timestamp":"2026-03-22T07:56:07.977Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see how it works. The `state` is a `ServerState` which is `Record<string, JSONValue[]>`. The handlers get the state passed in. The state is managed at the server level.\n\nThe key integration point is `schema-routes.ts` where the route handlers are created. The handlers receive `state: ServerState` and can access/modify the stored entities.\n\nWhat I need to do is:\n1. Add a `WorldState` instance to `ServerGenerator`\n2. Pass it to the route handlers somehow\n3. In `schema-routes.ts`, when generating objects, use the WorldState to resolve FKs\n\nBut looking at the architecture, the route handlers in `schema-routes.ts` receive `(req: RouteRequest, state: ServerState)` - they don't have access to a WorldState instance.\n\n\nI think the cleanest path is to store the WorldState directly on the ServerGenerator instance, then inject it through the route handler closure when they're created in `createRouteHandler`. I'd need to pass it as an additional parameter and thread it through from there.\n\nActually, looking at how handlers are created in schema-routes.ts, they already receive both `req` and `state`. The real solution is to attach the WorldState to the ServerState object itself under a special key like `_world`, so handlers can access it naturally without changing the signature. Then when `handlePost` or other methods register entities, they can update the world state at the same time. Let me check how `handlePost` works to see where the best integration point is.","thinkingSignature":"e4374d4e147badff3fecaf7238bed02d1c011f98e48a605f3a4e43d776531fa3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ff0e2ujybzvc_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\dev\\schemock-app\\src\\generators\\schema-routes.ts","offset":155,"limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"