{"type":"message","id":"c694a0cc","parentId":"ab5a8363","timestamp":"2026-03-22T08:01:47.734Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `resolveAndRegister` returns `JSONValue` (which includes null), but `data` is `NonNullJSONValue`. I need to fix the return type of `resolveAndRegister` to be `NonNullJSONValue`.\n\nLooking at my `resolveAndRegister` function:\n```typescript\nfunction resolveAndRegister(\n    entity: JSONValue,\n    resource: string,\n    world: WorldState\n): JSONValue {\n    if (!entity || typeof entity !== 'object' || Array.isArray(entity)) {\n        return entity;\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThe early return `return entity` - if entity is null/undefined, it returns it (bad). \n\nThe real problem is that the function returns `JSONValue` when it should return `NonNullJSONValue` since the entity parameter is already typed as `JSONValue` and I'm not actually filtering out nulls in the early return. The simplest fix is to change the return type to `NonNullJSONValue` and tighten the type guard so it only accepts actual objects and arrays, not null or undefined values. `NonNullJSONValue`.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The entity passed in is `JSONValue`. If it's null, the early return returns null. But in the places where `resolveAndRegister` is called, the entity is already known to be a non-null object (from `dataObj = data as Record<string, JSONValue>` and checking it's an object).\n\nSo the type cast in the calls is loose. The fix is to tighten the function:\n1. Change return type to `NonNullJSONValue`\n2. The early return for non-object entities - these shouldn't happen in practice but to satisfy the type system I need to cast.\n\nOR: I can just cast the return value at the call sites, since we know the entity being passed in is a non-null object.\n\nLooking at the original code, it didn't have this problem because it was just `state[resource].push(dataObj)` where `dataObj` is typed as `Record<string, JSONValue>`. My change introduced the `resolved` variable with type `JSONValue`, and assigning it to `data` which is `NonNullJSONValue` causes the type mismatch. The cleanest fix is changing `resolveAndRegister`'s return type to `NonNullJSONValue`, since in practice it only returns non-null values for objects anyway. I'll also tighten the early return to handle the type narrowing properly.","thinkingSignature":"869afc850ab8a530d4b0fae2b03adc836698d184228804b5d31842ba45fdde95"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jvzee8cwz4qs_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\dev\\schemock-app\\src\\generators\\schema-routes.ts","oldText":"function resolveAndRegister(\n    entity: JSONValue,\n    resource: string,\n    world: WorldState\n): JSONValue {\n    if (!entity || typeof entity !== 'object' || Array.isArray(entity)) {\n        return entity;\n    }\n\n    const obj = entity as Record<string, JSONValue>;\n    const resolved = { ...obj };\n\n    // Step 1: resolve FK fields → real IDs from the world\n    for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(resolved)) {\n        if (isIdField(key) && typeof value === 'string') {\n            const ref = detectForeignKey(key);\n            if (ref && world.hasEntities(ref)) {\n                const realEntity = world.getRandomEntity(ref);\n                if (realEntity && typeof realEntity === 'object' && 'id' in realEntity) {\n                    resolved[key] = String((realEntity as Record<string, JSONValue>).id);\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Step 2: register so future FK references can find this entity\n    world.register(worldResourceKey(resource), resolved);\n\n    return resolved;\n}","newText":"function resolveAndRegister(\n    entity: JSONValue,\n    resource: string,\n    world: WorldState\n): NonNullJSONValue {\n    if (!entity || typeof entity !== 'object' || Array.isArray(entity)) {\n        // Shouldn't happen for the call sites (objects only), but satisfy the type system\n        return entity as NonNullJSONValue;\n    }\n\n    const obj = entity as Record<string, JSONValue>;\n    const resolved = { ...obj };\n\n    // Step 1: resolve FK fields → real IDs from the world\n    for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(resolved)) {\n        if (isIdField(key) && typeof value === 'string') {\n            const ref = detectForeignKey(key);\n            if (ref && world.hasEntities(ref)) {\n                const realEntity = world.getRandomEntity(ref);\n                if (realEntity && typeof realEntity === 'object' && 'id' in realEntity) {\n                    resolved[key] = String((realEntity as Record<string, JSONValue>).id);\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Step 2: register so future FK references can find this entity\n    world.register(worldResourceKey(resource), resolved);\n\n    return resolved as NonNullJSONValue;\n}"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":82469,"output":1061,"cacheRead":12454,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95984,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774166482832}}
