{"type":"message","id":"6dab4ebf","parentId":"aec31858","timestamp":"2026-03-22T08:04:18.880Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Pushed! Now let me also push the temp landing page and README update from earlier. Wait, I already did that earlier. Let me verify what was pushed.\n\nActually wait - earlier I cloned to `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\schemocker` and pushed from there. But now I cloned fresh to `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\dev\\schemock-app` which is a separate clone. The README and index.html changes I made were in the temp directory, not in the dev one.\n\nLet me check if those changes are also in the dev clone...Actually, the README and index.html I pushed earlier were from the temp clone (`C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\schemocker`). The dev clone at `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\dev\\schemock-app` would be a fresh clone from GitHub, which would have pulled those changes already.\n\n\nSo the sequence was: I pushed the README and index.html updates from the temp directory first (which are now on GitHub), then cloned fresh to dev and implemented the world-state feature on top of that. The dev clone already has those earlier changes since it's pulling from the same remote.\n\nNow I should draft a summary for Zach about what's been completed.","thinkingSignature":"f0b3f1a4a15470078365e86712e7dfc67c997a872e4f3383dfcb8e7f9c514212"},{"type":"text","text":"Pushed ✅ Here's what landed:\n\n**3/22 04:00 AM — What got built:**\n\n**`world-state.ts` — Semantic cross-resource entity store (new file)**\n- Maintains entity pools per resource\n- FK patterns: `authorId` → `users`, `categoryId` → `categories`, etc. (24 patterns)\n- Every entity generated gets FK fields resolved to **real IDs** that exist in the world\n- Entities register on POST/GET so cross-references are always valid\n\n**`schema-routes.ts` — FK resolution wired into every entity creation**\n- `handleGetCollection`, `handleGetById`, `handlePost`, `handlePut` — all call `resolveAndRegister()`\n- Before: `authorId: \"xyz-123\"` → might not match any real user\n- After: `authorId: \"user-1\"` → guaranteed to match a real user in the pool\n\n**`mcp-server/index.ts` — New `world_snapshot` tool**\n- AI can call `world_snapshot()` and see: what resources exist, all their entity IDs, total count\n- So an AI knows exactly which user IDs to use when generating a post with `authorId`\n\n**`server.ts` — New `GET /__schemock/world` endpoint**\n- Exposes world state snapshot as JSON for the MCP tool\n\n**TypeScript: clean compile ✅**\n\n---\n\nThis is the foundation. The next layer (autonomous E2E test generation, semantic data with personality, schema inference from UI code) can all build on this. The world state is the differentiator — no other mock tool has it.\n\nGo sleep, Zach. Good news delivered. ✨"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":84349,"output":613,"cacheRead":12454,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97416,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774166640451}}
{"type":"message","id":"30caec69","parentId":"6dab4ebf","timestamp":"2026-03-22T08:04:19.604Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pushed ✅ Here's what landed:\n\n**3/22 04:00 AM — What got built:**\n\n**`world-state.ts` — Semantic cross-resource entity store (new file)**\n- Maintains entity pools per resource\n- FK patterns: `authorId` → `users`, `categoryId` → `categories`, etc. (24 patterns)\n- Every entity generated gets FK fields resolved to **real IDs** that exist in the world\n- Entities register on POST/GET so cross-references are always valid\n\n**`schema-routes.ts` — FK resolution wired into every entity creation**\n- `handleGetCollection`, `handleGetById`, `handlePost`, `handlePut` — all call `resolveAndRegister()`\n- Before: `authorId: \"xyz-123\"` → might not match any real user\n- After: `authorId: \"user-1\"` → guaranteed to match a real user in the pool\n\n**`mcp-server/index.ts` — New `world_snapshot` tool**\n- AI can call `world_snapshot()` and see: what resources exist, all their entity IDs, total count\n- So an AI knows exactly which user IDs to use when generating a post with `authorId`\n\n**`server.ts` — New `GET /__schemock/world` endpoint**\n- Exposes world state snapshot as JSON for the MCP tool\n\n**TypeScript: clean compile ✅**\n\n---\n\nThis is the foundation. The next layer (autonomous E2E test generation, semantic data with personality, schema inference from UI code) can all build on this. The world state is the differentiator — no other mock tool has it.\n\nGo sleep, Zach. Good news delivered. ✨"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774166659604}}
