{"type":"message","id":"2ec91a7c","parentId":"e8160108","timestamp":"2026-03-22T14:49:32.217Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me build Phase 1. I'll start with the `generate component` command. Here's my plan:\n\n1. Create a new CLI command `schemock generate component [endpoint]`\n2. It needs to:\n   - Call the mock server endpoint\n   - Use the schema to generate TypeScript types\n   - Use the response to generate a React component\n3. For the AI generation, I'll use a simple approach: generate the component using template-based generation since calling an LLM from a CLI is complex. But actually, I should use a more practical approach.\n\nWait - for `schemock generate component` to work as an AI feature, I need to think about this carefully. \n\nI'm realizing the CLI approach needs to handle the LLM integration carefully - I can use environment variables for API keys and implement streaming output with clear fallbacks when keys aren't available. For the MVP, I'll focus on a straightforward implementation that either prompts for a key or gracefully degrades.\n\nThe architecture should distinguish between the local `schemock generate` command that makes direct HTTP calls to a running mock server, versus the MCP server integration that handles tool definitions. I'm planning to build this in phases: starting with a CLI command that accepts endpoint and schema inputs, making the HTTP request, then using template-based TypeScript interface generation from the schema structure.\n\nFor React component generation, I'll leverage the schema types and API response structure to create sensible defaults without requiring an LLM, while leaving the AI integration path open for users who want more sophisticated generation through their own API keys. The key is keeping the MVP lean—a `generate component [endpoint]` command that hits the running server, inspects the schema, and outputs a basic typed React component users can extend. I'll start by building the generate command, then move into schema-to-types conversion and finally E2E test generation.","thinkingSignature":"d151948798d03ddcf55c5c862e8b4d3175c3877ab125f5de41afee93c5418763"},{"type":"text","text":"On it. Let me pull the latest and start building Phase 1.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l78srw600er9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\dev\\schemock-app; git pull origin main 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":447,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":91308,"totalTokens":96044,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774190951897}}
