{"type":"message","id":"47f15488","parentId":"90424272","timestamp":"2026-03-22T14:51:31.089Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Everything is already built! The server.ts has all the endpoints:\n- `GET /__schemock/world` ✅\n- `GET /__schemock/schema` ✅\n- `POST /__schemock/reload` ✅\n- `POST /__schemock/seed` ✅\n\nThe entire AI-native infrastructure is already there. The MCP server has all 7 tools. The AI adapters are built. The schema-inferrer is built.\n\nSo what's missing? Let me check the PLAN.md checklist:\n\n| # | Task | Status |\n\n\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | Write `src/ai/provider.ts` interface | ✅ Already built |\n| 2 | Write `src/ai/openai.ts` adapter | ✅ Already built |\n| 3 | Add 3 MCP tools to `src/mcp-server/index.ts` | ✅ Already built |\n| 4 | Wire `generate_schema` to schema-inferrer | ✅ Already wired |\n| 5 | `schemock init \"NL description\"` CLI command | ❓ Need to check |\n| 6 | Semantic field detector in `schema-routes.ts` | ❓ Need to check |\n| 7 | `seed_world` MCP tool → world-state | ✅ Already built |\n| 8 | `ollama.ts` adapter | ✅ Already built |\n| 9 | README rewrite | ✅ Done (I did this last night) |\n| 10 | `vllm.ts` adapter | ❓ Deferred |\n\nLooking at the remaining items, I see that the Ollama adapter is done, the README is updated, but the vLLM adapter is deferred and there are a few other tasks still pending. I should focus on what's actually needed rather than what's missing from the original plan. Let me think about what could be built next.\n\nI notice the `schemock init \"NL description\"` command isn't in the CLI yet, so I could add that. The semantic field detection for AI enrichment is also missing. But wait—the stash had modifications to `src/mcp-server/index.ts`, and after stashing and pulling, those changes disappeared. My world_snapshot fixes weren't actually applied to the remote. I need to check what's currently on the remote branch to see the actual state of things.\n\nThe `git stash show` output shows a diff on `handleWorldSnapshot` that was stashed, but then I did a `git stash drop` to discard it, so those local changes are gone now.\n\nThe remote version already has `const { resource, sample = false } = args || {};` which is the correct state. But I need to check what else is missing - the `schemock init` command with the NL description feature isn't in the CLI, and the semantic field detector for AI enrichment isn't in schema-routes.ts yet. Let me prioritize what's actually needed for the product to work.\n\nLooking at the MCP server, the AI module is loaded via a dynamic require that tries to import from the compiled JavaScript files in the build directory. If the TypeScript source files haven't been compiled yet, those imports would fail and the AI features wouldn't be available at all. So the priority should be making sure the build pipeline compiles everything properly and then tackling the two missing pieces: the NL description init command and the semantic field detection. I need to rebuild the MCP server file since my changes were stashed and then overwritten when I pulled. The remote already has the world_snapshot implementation, so I need to reapply my fixes to the `sample` variable handling on top of what's there.\n\nLooking at the actual plan, the core features seem to be already built out, so let me verify what's genuinely missing rather than assuming there's major work left to do. Looking at what's actually missing from the full plan, there are three concrete gaps: the CLI doesn't have a `schemock init` command for natural language descriptions, the semantic field detector isn't in schema-routes.ts, and the vllm adapter isn't built yet (though that was marked as deferred anyway).\n\nThe MCP server's AI module references are also using outdated `.js` extensions instead of `.ts`, but that's a build configuration issue. The most pressing things to tackle are getting the CLI command working, adding the field detector, and making sure the AI provider resolution is solid.\n\nFor `schemock init`, I need to wire up the schema-inferrer to take a natural language description and convert it into a schema that can be saved to disk and hot-reloaded into the server. The semantic field detector would intercept field generation and enhance semantic fields like bio or description using the AI provider instead of relying on basic faker logic.","thinkingSignature":"f3a17d4681484dd00739ffe471ba491bc7889bc6a4bbca908788db8cdea85de9"},{"type":"text","text":"This is much further along than I thought. Everything's there. Let me check what's actually missing vs the plan:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yryba84wuy6n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\dev\\schemock-app; Select-String -Path \"src/cli/index.ts\" -Pattern \"init.*nl|describe.*api|generate_schema\" -Context 2,2"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yryba84wuy6n_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\dev\\schemock-app; Select-String -Path \"src/generators/schema-routes.ts\" -Pattern \"semantic|bio|description|fieldEnrich|ai.*enrich\" -Context 2,2"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91368,"output":1110,"cacheRead":12454,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104932,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774191052451}}
