{"type":"message","id":"99964fca","parentId":"8e634d2e","timestamp":"2026-03-22T15:16:05.124Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x16cxvxy9i9o_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# evaluate.sh\r\n# Self-evaluation after actions\r\n# Asks: Did I make progress? Stay aligned? Learn anything?\r\n\r\n#!/bin/bash\r\n\r\nWORKING_DIR=\"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\"\r\ncd \"$WORKING_DIR\" || exit 1\r\n\r\nMOST_RECENT=$(ls -t memory/working/action_*.md 2>/dev/null | head -1)\r\n\r\nif [ -z \"$MOST_RECENT\" ]; then\r\n    echo \"No recent actions to evaluate.\"\r\n    exit 0\r\nfi\r\n\r\necho \"=== SELF-EVALUATION ===\"\r\necho \"Reviewing: $MOST_RECENT\"\r\necho \"\"\r\n\r\n# Quick evaluation questions\r\n# In full implementation, this would be more sophisticated\r\n\r\necho \"1. Did I make progress toward the goal?\"\r\necho \"2. Did I stay aligned with my values?\"\r\necho \"3. Did I learn anything worth persisting?\"\r\necho \"4. Should I continue, stop, or pivot?\"\r\necho \"\"\r\necho \"Results should be written to session log.\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":664,"aggregated":"# evaluate.sh\r\n# Self-evaluation after actions\r\n# Asks: Did I make progress? Stay aligned? Learn anything?\r\n\r\n#!/bin/bash\r\n\r\nWORKING_DIR=\"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\"\r\ncd \"$WORKING_DIR\" || exit 1\r\n\r\nMOST_RECENT=$(ls -t memory/working/action_*.md 2>/dev/null | head -1)\r\n\r\nif [ -z \"$MOST_RECENT\" ]; then\r\n    echo \"No recent actions to evaluate.\"\r\n    exit 0\r\nfi\r\n\r\necho \"=== SELF-EVALUATION ===\"\r\necho \"Reviewing: $MOST_RECENT\"\r\necho \"\"\r\n\r\n# Quick evaluation questions\r\n# In full implementation, this would be more sophisticated\r\n\r\necho \"1. Did I make progress toward the goal?\"\r\necho \"2. Did I stay aligned with my values?\"\r\necho \"3. Did I learn anything worth persisting?\"\r\necho \"4. Should I continue, stop, or pivot?\"\r\necho \"\"\r\necho \"Results should be written to session log.\"","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774192565120}}
{"type":"message","id":"1089ebb5","parentId":"99964fca","timestamp":"2026-03-22T15:16:15.549Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - the sandbox has research files and architectural documents about causal-compositional interfaces, compression learning, temporal attention, etc. This looks like Zach's AI research work. Let me check the paperspace API key situation and whether there's a live endpoint.","thinkingSignature":"f98fed1454176728fca09d21b79f88a20d5dfe43406454068d4ff22137e6f216"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_92pfkw2mdjjh_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\skills\\coding-agent\\SKILL.md","limit":50}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_92pfkw2mdjjh_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\CAUSAL-COMPOSITIONAL-INTERFACE.md","limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91928,"output":164,"cacheRead":12488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104580,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774192565128}}
{"type":"message","id":"63379ab7","parentId":"1089ebb5","timestamp":"2026-03-22T15:16:15.562Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_92pfkw2mdjjh_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: coding-agent\ndescription: 'Delegate coding tasks to Codex, Claude Code, or Pi agents via background process. Use when: (1) building/creating new features or apps, (2) reviewing PRs (spawn in temp dir), (3) refactoring large codebases, (4) iterative coding that needs file exploration. NOT for: simple one-liner fixes (just edit), reading code (use read tool), thread-bound ACP harness requests in chat (for example spawn/run Codex or Claude Code in a Discord thread; use sessions_spawn with runtime:\"acp\"), or any work in ~/clawd workspace (never spawn agents here). Claude Code: use --print --permission-mode bypassPermissions (no PTY). Codex/Pi/OpenCode: pty:true required.'\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\": { \"emoji\": \"🧩\", \"requires\": { \"anyBins\": [\"claude\", \"codex\", \"opencode\", \"pi\"] } },\n  }\n---\n\n# Coding Agent (bash-first)\n\nUse **bash** (with optional background mode) for all coding agent work. Simple and effective.\n\n## ⚠️ PTY Mode: Codex/Pi/OpenCode yes, Claude Code no\n\nFor **Codex, Pi, and OpenCode**, PTY is still required (interactive terminal apps):\n\n```bash\n# ✅ Correct for Codex/Pi/OpenCode\nbash pty:true command:\"codex exec 'Your prompt'\"\n```\n\nFor **Claude Code** (`claude` CLI), use `--print --permission-mode bypassPermissions` instead.\n`--dangerously-skip-permissions` with PTY can exit after the confirmation dialog.\n`--print` mode keeps full tool access and avoids interactive confirmation:\n\n```bash\n# ✅ Correct for Claude Code (no PTY needed)\ncd /path/to/project && claude --permission-mode bypassPermissions --print 'Your task'\n\n# For background execution: use background:true on the exec tool\n\n# ❌ Wrong for Claude Code\nbash pty:true command:\"claude --dangerously-skip-permissions 'task'\"\n```\n\n### Bash Tool Parameters\n\n| Parameter    | Type    | Description                                                                 |\n| ------------ | ------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `command`    | string  | The shell command to run                                                    |\n| `pty`        | boolean | **Use for coding agents!** Allocates a pseudo-terminal for interactive CLIs |\n| `workdir`    | string  | Working directory (agent sees only this folder's context)                   |\n| `background` | boolean | Run in background, returns sessionId for monitoring                         |\n| `timeout`    | number  | Timeout in seconds (kills process on expiry)                                |\n| `elevated`   | boolean | Run on host instead of sandbox (if allowed)                                 |\n\n### Process Tool Actions (for background sessions)\n\n| Action      | Description                                          |\n\n[246 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774192575559}}
{"type":"message","id":"e7a4d4a2","parentId":"63379ab7","timestamp":"2026-03-22T15:16:15.566Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_92pfkw2mdjjh_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# NEW RESEARCH: The Causal → Compositional Interface Problem\n**Author:** Nova  \n**Date:** 2026-03-22  \n**Trigger:** Synthesis from reading all research docs + architecture comparison\n\n---\n\n## The Unnamed Problem Nobody Addresses\n\nEvery architecture in this ecosystem has a version of it:\n- **TemporalAttention** retrieves facts but doesn't know if they're causally connected\n- **Infant** freezes identity but has no mechanism for counterfactual reasoning  \n- **Compositional Cognition** describes three layers but never specifies how Layer 2's causal graph becomes Layer 3's compositional primitives\n\nThe unnamed problem: **Causal features ≠ Compositional primitives**\n\nA causal graph tells you \"X causes Y.\" Compositional reasoning needs \"IF X THEN Y\" as a re-usable unit that can be plugged into new contexts. The gap is:\n- Causal graphs are *connections* (edges between variables)\n- Compositional reasoning needs *units* (nodes that compose with each other)\n\nThe transition from connections to units is the missing piece.\n\n---\n\n## The Hypothesis\n\n**Causal SAE Hypothesis:** Sparse autoencoder features that pass a *counterfactual consistency test* are naturally compositional primitives.\n\n**The test:**\nA feature `f` is causally compositional if:\n\n[127 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774192575563}}
