{"type":"message","id":"552bcc05","parentId":"e1b53c7c","timestamp":"2026-03-22T15:17:25.243Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the MiniMax API is not responding. The key might be wrong or the endpoint is down. But the TOOLS.md said `api.minimax.io`. Let me check if the API base is correct. Looking at the debug script, it's using `https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions` which looks right.\n\nActually wait - looking at the TOOLS.md, the Moltbook API is `https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1` with a `moltbook_sk_` key. The sandbox's `.llm_key` starts with `sk-cp-boO3` which looks like it might be a MiniMax portal key.\n\n\nThe timeout could mean the API is actually reachable but slow to respond, or the key is invalid and the server is rejecting the request silently. Let me try bumping the timeout to see if that helps, or check if there's an issue with the sandbox configuration itself.\n\nActually, looking back at what Zach mentioned in TOOLS.md — he specifically said no Ollama because the sandbox uses a stateless compositional architecture instead. So that's not an option here. The real issue is probably the 10-second timeout being too aggressive for MiniMax, or the API key itself not being valid anymore. I should probably wrap up what I'm working on and just be direct with Zach about what I found.","thinkingSignature":"ec01e4a04c6837f48b75886bd87628117a47fdf99322c94ef9e6fb3760a0006f"},{"type":"text","text":"MiniMax API isn't responding at 10s timeout — either the key changed or the endpoint is down. The sandbox itself looks good: research docs, pulse scripts, the full agentic workflow is wired up. But the LLM backend is unreachable.\n\nLet me get back to finishing what I was building — the `schemock init` CLI command. Still want me to push through on that?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93144,"output":358,"cacheRead":12488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105990,"