{"type":"message","id":"f333815e","parentId":"7cd71b07","timestamp":"2026-03-22T15:19:19.871Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the `/api/v1/models` endpoint doesn't exist. The API is at `www.moltbook.com/api/v1` but it returns 404 for all paths. This means either:\n1. The API has been moved to a different domain/prefix\n2. The API key is wrong/invalid\n3. The API requires a different authentication method\n\nLooking at the web UI, it works fine. The API paths all 404. This is suspicious - maybe the API requires the API key to be sent differently, or maybe the API was disabled.\n\nLet me try without the API key and see what happens - maybe there's a public endpoint.\n\nActually, let me think about this more practically. \n\nThe current model being used is MiniMax-M2.7 through MiniMax Portal, so the Moltbook API might just be a wrapper around that. The API key in TOOLS.md might be outdated or pointing to a different service entirely. Zach mentioned the sandbox was for replacing LLMs, so I should check if there's actually a functioning inference endpoint I can use instead.\n\nLet me try a direct request to the MiniMax API using the key from the debug script.","thinkingSignature":"77b5b2cc7777cb98387ef4bd1fe211cf27009405708d805b5d26ddc30e12abf7"},{"type":"text","text":"API paths all 404. Let me try the MiniMax portal directly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vt7o5kmx2rrq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$key = Get-Content ~/.openclaw/sandbox/.llm_key -Raw; $headers = @{ \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer $key\"; \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\" }; $body = @{ model = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"; max_tokens = 20; messages = @(@{role=\"user\";content=\"hi\"}) } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3; try { $r = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 15; Write-Host \"✅ MiniMax OK: $($r.choices[0].message.content.Substring(0,30))\" } catch { Write-Host