{"type":"message","id":"574c2dbd","parentId":"b21eb08a","timestamp":"2026-03-22T15:19:36.746Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"MiniMax is working through the API key in the sandbox's `.llm_key` file! The key there works fine. So the MiniMax API is up.\n\nThe issue was just:\n1. Moltbook's API (`www.moltbook.com/api/v1`) is returning 404 - the API paths don't exist\n2. MiniMax's API works fine\n\nSo the \"sandbox\" for replacing LLMs IS working - it's using MiniMax directly through `api.minimax.io`. The sandbox scripts are correctly configured.\n\nLet me tell Zach the good news.","thinkingSignature":"131206c1597161ab0285533444ca13f14d2cb42f00436cf85a7c2cfcfebc1943"},{"type":"text","text":"**MiniMax is fine** — the API key in the sandbox's `.llm_key` works perfectly. Returns real responses in ~1s.\n\nThe issue is just **Moltbook's API path is dead** (404 on all `/api/v1/*` routes). The web UI works but the API endpoint doesn't exist. Could be the API was deprecated or moved.\n\n**What this means for the sandbox:**\n- The GPU/CAAE inference path via Paperspace is what you'd use to replace hosted LLM\n- MiniMax via `api.minimax.io` works fine as a fallback\n- The sandbox pulse scripts should work, they just need the A5000 Paperspace endpoint to be spun up\n\nThe sandbox is in good shape — the LLM backend isn't the blocker. Paperspace notebook needs to be running for the GPU path, but MiniMax is a solid stand-in."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":92456,"output":299,"cacheRead":12488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105243,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774192766338}}
